#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "&UML; Basics"
msgstr "&UML; Osnove"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid "About &UML;"
msgstr "O &UML;"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter will give you a quick overview of the basics of &UML;. Keep in "
"mind that this is not a comprehensive tutorial on &UML; but rather a brief "
"introduction to &UML; which can be read as a &UML; tutorial. If you would "
"like to learn more about the Unified Modelling Language, or in general about "
"software analysis and design, refer to one of the many books available on "
"the topic. There are also a lot of tutorials on the Internet which you can "
"take as a starting point."
msgstr ""
"Ovo poglavlje će vam dati brzi pregled osnove &UML;. Imajte na umu da ovo "
"nije sveobuhvatan tutorial o &UML; već kratak uvod u &UML; koji se može "
"čitati i kao &UML; tutorial. Ako želite saznati više o Unified Modeling "
"Language, ili općenito o softver za analizu i dizajn, odnose se na jedan od "
"mnogih knjiga dostupnih na tu temu. Tu su i dosta tutoriali na internetu "
"koje možete uzeti kao polazište."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Unified Modelling Language (&UML;) is a diagramming language or notation "
"to specify, visualize and document models of Object Oriented software "
"systems. &UML; is not a development method, that means it does not tell you "
"what to do first and what to do next or how to design your system, but it "
"helps you to visualize your design and communicate with others. &UML; is "
"controlled by the Object Management Group (<acronym>OMG</acronym>) and is "
"the industry standard for graphically describing software."
msgstr ""
"The Unified Modeling Language (&UML;) je diagramski jezik ili notacija za "
"specificiranje, vizualiziranje i dokumentaju modela Objektno Orientisanih "
"softverskih sistema. &UML; nije razvojna metoda, to znači da vam ne kaže šta "
"da radite prvo i šta sljedeće ili uči kako da dizajnirate svoj sistem, ali "
"će Vam pomoći da vizualizirate svoj dizajn i komunicirate s drugima. &UML; "
"kontrolira Management Group objekta (<acronym>OMG</acronym>) i predstavlja "
"industrijski standard za grafički opis softvera."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&UML; is designed for Object Oriented software design and has limited use "
"for other programming paradigms."
msgstr ""
"&UML; je dizajniran za Objektno Orijentisani dizajn softvera i ima "
"ograničenu upotrebu za druge programske paradigme ."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&UML; is composed of many model elements that represent the different parts "
"of a software system. The &UML; elements are used to create diagrams, which "
"represent a certain part, or a point of view of the system. The following "
"types of diagrams are supported by &umbrello;:"
msgstr ""
"&UML; sastoji se od mnogo elemenata modela koji predstavljaju različite "
"dijelove softvera sistema. The &UML; elementi se koriste za kreiranje "
"dijagrama, koji predstavljaju određeni dio, ili stanovišta sistema. Sljedeće "
"vrste dijagrama su podržani od strane &umbrello;:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"use-case-diagram\">Use Case Diagrams</link></"
"emphasis> show actors (people or other users of the system), use cases (the "
"scenarios when they use the system), and their relationships"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"koristi-case-dijagram\">Use Case Dijagrami</link></"
"emphasis>prikazuje aktere (ljudi ili drugim korisnicima sistema), korištenje "
"predmeta (scenariji kada koriste sistem), i njihove odnose"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"class-diagram\">Class Diagrams</link></emphasis> "
"show classes and the relationships between them"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"klas-dijagram\">Dijagram Klasa</link></emphasis> "
"prikazuje klase i odnosa između njih"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"sequence-diagram\">Sequence Diagrams</link></"
"emphasis> show objects and a sequence of method calls they make to other "
"objects."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"sequence-diagram\">Sekvencni dijagram</link></"
"emphasis> prikazuje objekat i niz metoda poziva oni čine na druge objekte."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"collaboration-diagram\">Collaboration Diagrams</"
"link></emphasis> show objects and their relationship, putting emphasis on "
"the objects that participate in the message exchange"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"collaboration-diagram\">Dijagram saradnje</link></"
"emphasis> vrši prikaz objekata i njihovih odnosa, stavljajući naglasak na "
"objektima koje sudjeluju u razmjeni poruka"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"state-diagram\">State Diagrams</link></emphasis> "
"show states, state changes and events in an object or a part of the system"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"state-diagram\">Dijagram stanja</link></emphasis> "
"prikazuje stanja, promjena stanja i događaja u objektu ili dio sistema"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"activity-diagram\">Activity Diagrams</link></"
"emphasis> show activities and the changes from one activity to another with "
"the events occurring in some part of the system"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"activity-diagram\">Dijagram aktivnosti</link></"
"emphasis> prikazuje aktivnosti i promjene iz jedne aktivnosti na drugu sa "
"događajima koji se dešavaju u nekim dijelovima sistema"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"component-diagram\">Component Diagrams</link></"
"emphasis> show the high level programming components (such as KParts or Java "
"Beans)."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"component-diagram\">Dijagram komponenti</link></"
"emphasis> pokazuje programske komponente na visokoj razini (kao što su "
"KParts ili Java Beans)."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"deployment-diagram\">Deployment Diagrams</link></"
"emphasis> show the instances of the components and their relationships."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"deployment-diagram\">Dijagram isporuke</link></"
"emphasis> pokazuje instance komponenti i njihove odnose."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"entity-relationship-diagram\">Entity Relationship "
"Diagrams</link></emphasis> show data and the relationships and constraints "
"between the data."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"entity-relationship-diagram\">Entity Relationship "
"Diagrams</link></emphasis>prikazuje podatke i odnose i ograničenja između "
"podataka."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "&UML; Elements"
msgstr "&UML; Elementi"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case Diagram"
msgstr "Dijagram slučaja upotrebe"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use Case Diagrams describe the relationships and dependencies between a "
"group of <emphasis>Use Cases</emphasis> and the Actors participating in the "
"process."
msgstr ""
"Dijagram slučaja upotrebe opisuju odnose i ovisnosti između grupe "
"<emphasis>Use Cases</emphasis> i akteri koji učestvuju u tom procesu."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is important to notice that Use Case Diagrams are not suited to represent "
"the design, and cannot describe the internals of a system. Use Case Diagrams "
"are meant to facilitate the communication with the future users of the "
"system, and with the customer, and are specially helpful to determine the "
"required features the system is to have. Use Case Diagrams tell, "
"<emphasis>what</emphasis> the system should do but do not &mdash; and cannot "
"&mdash; specify <emphasis>how</emphasis> this is to be achieved."
msgstr ""
"Važno je primjetiti da Use Case Dijagrami nisu pogodni da predstavljaju "
"dizajna, i ne mogu opisati unutrašnji sistema. Use Case Dijagrami su značilo "
"da se olakša komunikaciju sa budućim korisnicima sistema, i sa kupcem, a "
"posebno su korisne za određivanje potrebne ima sistem je da se. Use Case "
"Dijagrami reći, <emphasis>what</emphasis> sistem treba učiniti, ali ne "
"&mdash; i ne može &mdash; navesti <emphasis>how</emphasis> ovo se želi "
"postići."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example Use Case diagram."
msgstr "Primjer Dijagrama slučaja upotrebe."

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing a Use Case Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikazuje Dijagram slučaja upotrebe</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing a Use Case Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikazuje Dijagram slučaja upotrebe</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case"
msgstr "Slučaj upotrebe"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <emphasis>Use Case</emphasis> describes &mdash; from the point of view of "
"the actors &mdash; a group of activities in a system that produces a "
"concrete, tangible result."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Use Case</emphasis> opisuje &mdash; iz ugla aktera &mdash; grupu "
"aktivnosti u sistemu koji proizvodi konkretan, opipljiv rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use Cases are descriptions of the typical interactions between the users of "
"a system and the system itself. They represent the external interface of the "
"system and specify a form of requirements of what the system has to do "
"(remember, only what, not how)."
msgstr ""
"Koristite Slučajevi su opisi tipičnih interakcije između korisnika sustava i "
"samog sistema. Oni predstavljaju vanjskog sučelje sistema i odredite oblik "
"zahtjeva onoga sistema ima veze (zapamtite, samo ono, a ne kako)."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When working with Use Cases, it is important to remember some simple rules:"
msgstr ""
"Prilikom rada sa Use Cases, važno je imati na umu nekoliko jednostavnih "
"pravila:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each Use Case is related to at least one actor"
msgstr "Svaki Use Case se odnosi na najmanje jednog aktera"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each Use Case has an initiator (&ie; an actor)"
msgstr "Svaki Use Case ima inicijator (&ie; akter)"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each Use Case leads to a relevant result (a result with <quote>business "
"value</quote>)"
msgstr ""
"Svaki Use Case dovodi do relevantnih rezultata (a rezultat s <quote>poslovnu "
"vrijednost</quote>)"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use Cases can also have relationships with other Use Cases. The three most "
"typical types of relationships between Use Cases are:"
msgstr ""
"Koristite slučajevima i može imati odnose s drugim Use Cases. Tri "
"najtipičniji vrste odnosa između korištenja Cases su:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>&lt;&lt;include&gt;&gt;</emphasis> which specifies that a Use Case "
"takes place <emphasis>inside</emphasis> another Use Case"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>&lt;&lt;include&gt;&gt;</emphasis> koji određuje da se odvija a "
"Use Case <emphasis>u</emphasis> drugom Use Case"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>&lt;&lt;extends&gt;&gt;</emphasis> which specifies that in certain "
"situations, or at some point (called an extension point) a Use Case will be "
"extended by another."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>&lt;&lt;extends&gt;&gt;</emphasis> koji određuje da u određenim "
"situacijama, ili u nekom trenutku (naziva tačku proširenja) a Use Case će se "
"produžiti za još."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Generalization</emphasis> specifies that a Use Case inherits the "
"characteristics of the <quote>Super</quote>-Use Case, and can override some "
"of them or add new ones in a similar way as the inheritance between classes."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Generalizacija </emphasis> navodi da u Use Case nasljeđuje "
"karakteristike <quote>Super</quote>-Use Case, i može nadjačati neke od njih "
"ili dodati nove na sličan način kao i nasljeđivanja između klasa."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Actor"
msgstr "Učesnik"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An actor is an external entity (outside of the system) that interacts with "
"the system by participating (and often initiating) a Use Case. Actors can be "
"in real life people (for example users of the system), other computer "
"systems or external events."
msgstr ""
"Učesnik je vanjskog entiteta (izvan sistema) koji u interakciji sa sustavom "
"učestvujući (a često i pokretanje) a Use Case. Akteri mogu biti u stvarnom "
"životu ljudi (npr korisnici sistema), drugih računalnih sustava ili "
"eksternih događaja."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Actors do not represent the <emphasis>physical</emphasis> people or systems, "
"but their <emphasis>role</emphasis>. This means that when a person interacts "
"with the system in different ways (assuming different roles) he will be "
"represented by several actors. For example a person that gives customer "
"support by the telephone and takes orders from the customer into the system "
"would be represented by an actor <quote>Support Staff</quote> and an actor "
"<quote>Sales Representative</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Glumci ne predstavljaju <emphasis> fizičke </emphasis> ljudi ili sistema, "
"ali njihova <emphasis> ulogu </emphasis>. To znači da kada osoba komunicira "
"sa sistemom na različite načine (pod pretpostavkom različite uloge) da će "
"biti predstavljena nekoliko aktera. Na primjer, osoba koja daje podršku "
"kupcu od strane telefona i uzima naredbe od kupaca u sustav će biti "
"predstavljena glumac <quote> pomoćno osoblje </quote> i glumac <quote> "
"Prodaja predstavnik </quote>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Case Description"
msgstr "Use Case Opis"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use Case Descriptions are textual narratives of the Use Case. They usually "
"take the form of a note or a document that is somehow linked to the Use "
"Case, and explains the processes or activities that take place in the Use "
"Case."
msgstr ""
"Use Case Opisi su tekstualni narativa od Use Case. Oni su obično u obliku "
"note ili dokument koji je na neki način povezana sa Use Case, i objašnjava "
"procese ili aktivnosti koje se odvijaju u Use Case."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Class Diagram"
msgstr "Dijagram klasa"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Class Diagrams show the different classes that make up a system and how they "
"relate to each other. Class Diagrams are said to be <quote>static</quote> "
"diagrams because they show the classes, along with their methods and "
"attributes as well as the static relationships between them: which classes "
"<quote>know</quote> about which classes or which classes <quote>are part</"
"quote> of another class, but do not show the method calls between them."
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami klasa pokazuju različite klase koje čine sistem i kako se oni "
"odnose jedni prema drugima. Class Dijagrami se kaže da su <quote>statičke</"
"quote> dijagrama jer pokazuju klasa, zajedno sa svojim metodama i atribute, "
"kao i statičke odnosa između njih: što nastava <quote>zna</quote> o kojima "
"klase ili koja klase <quote>su dio</quote> druge klase, ali ne pokazuju "
"metodu poziva između njih."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example of a Class Diagram"
msgstr "Primjer dijagrama klasa"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing a Class Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikazivanje Dijagrama Klasa</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing a Class Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikazivanje Dijagrama Klasa</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Class"
msgstr "Klasa"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Class defines the attributes and the methods of a set of objects. All "
"objects of this class (instances of this class) share the same behavior, and "
"have the same set of attributes (each object has its own set). The term "
"<quote>Type</quote> is sometimes used instead of Class, but it is important "
"to mention that these two are not the same, and Type is a more general term."
msgstr ""
"A klasa definira atribute i metode skupa objekata. Svi objekti ove klase "
"(instance ove klase) dijele istu ponašanje, i imaju isti skup atributa "
"(svaki objekt ima svoj set). Izraz <quote>Tip</quote> se ponekad koristi "
"umjesto klase, ali je važno napomenuti da ova dva nisu iste, i tip je više "
"opšti pojam."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, Classes are represented by rectangles, with the name of the class, "
"and can also show the attributes and operations of the class in two other "
"<quote>compartments</quote> inside the rectangle."
msgstr ""
"U &UML;, Nastava se zastupa pravougaonika, sa imenom klase, a može se "
"pokazati atribute i operacije klase u unutar druga dva pravougaonika <quote> "
"pregrade </quote>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Class in &UML;"
msgstr "Klasa u &UML;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Visual representation of a Class in &UML;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase> Vizualna predstava klase u &UML;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Visual representation of a Class in &UML;</para>"
msgstr "<para> Vizualna predstava klase u &UML;</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attributes"
msgstr "Atributi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, Attributes are shown with at least their name, and can also show "
"their type, initial value and other properties. Attributes can also be "
"displayed with their visibility:"
msgstr ""
"U &UML;, atributi su prikazani sa najmanje njihovo ime, a može i pokazati "
"svoje vrste, početna vrijednost i drugih svojstava. Atributi mogu također "
"biti prikazani sa svojim vidljivosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>+</literal> Stands for <emphasis>public</emphasis> attributes"
msgstr "<literal>+</literal> Predstavlja <emphasis>javne</emphasis> atribute"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>#</literal> Stands for <emphasis>protected</emphasis> attributes"
msgstr "<literal>#</literal> Stalci za <emphasis>zaštićena</emphasis> atributa"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-</literal> Stands for <emphasis>private</emphasis> attributes"
msgstr ""
"<literal>-</literal> Predstavlja <emphasis>privatne</emphasis> atribute"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Operations"
msgstr "Operacije"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operations (methods) are also displayed with at least their name, and can "
"also show their parameters and return types. Operations can, just as "
"Attributes, display their visibility:"
msgstr ""
"Operacije (metode) su također prikazani sa najmanje njihovo ime, a može i "
"pokazati svoje parametre i povratak vrste. Operacije se, baš kao atributi, "
"prikazati njihove vidljivosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>+</literal> Stands for <emphasis>public</emphasis> operations"
msgstr "<literal>+</literal> Stalci za <emphasis>javno</emphasis> oepracije"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>#</literal> Stands for <emphasis>protected</emphasis> operations"
msgstr ""
"<literal>#</literal> Stalci za <emphasis>zaštićena</emphasis> operacije"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-</literal> Stands for <emphasis>private</emphasis> operations"
msgstr ""
"<literal>-</literal> Stalci za <emphasis>privatnih</emphasis> operacija"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Templates"
msgstr "Šabloni"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Classes can have templates, a value which is used for an unspecified class "
"or type. The template type is specified when a class is initiated (&ie; an "
"object is created). Templates exist in modern C++ and will be introduced in "
"Java 1.5 where they will be called Generics."
msgstr ""
"Klase mogu imati predloške, vrijednost koja se koristi za nenavedenu klasu "
"ili tip. Tip predloška je naveden kada je pokrenuta klase (&ie; kreiran je "
"objekt). Predlošci postoje u modernom C ++ i da biti će uvedeni u Java 1.5 "
"gdje će se zvati generici."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Class Associations"
msgstr "Pridruženja klasa"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Classes can relate (be associated with) to each other in different ways:"
msgstr ""
"Klase mogu biti vezane (biti pridružene s) jedne s drugima na različite "
"načine:"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Generalization</title>"
msgstr "<title>Generalizacija</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Inheritance is one of the fundamental concepts of Object Oriented "
"programming, in which a class <quote>gains</quote> all of the attributes and "
"operations of the class it inherits from, and can override/modify some of "
"them, as well as add more attributes and operations of its own."
msgstr ""
"Nasljeđivanje je jedan od osnovnih koncepata Object Oriented programiranja, "
"u kojoj klasi <quote>dobici</quote> sve atribute i operacije u razredu ga "
"nasljeduje od, i može nadjačati / mijenjati neke od njih, kao i add više "
"atributa i operacija vlastitih."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, a <emphasis>Generalization</emphasis> association between two "
"classes puts them in a hierarchy representing the concept of inheritance of "
"a derived class from a base class. In &UML;, Generalizations are represented "
"by a line connecting the two classes, with an arrow on the side of the base "
"class."
msgstr ""
"U &UML;, a <emphasis>Generalizacija</emphasis> povezanost između dvije klase "
"ih stavlja u hijerarhiji predstavlja koncept nasljeđivanja je izvedena klasa "
"iz baze klase. U &UML;, generalizacije predstavljena linija koja povezuje "
"dvije klase, sa strelicom na strani bazne klase."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Generalization</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Generalizacija</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Visual representation of a generalization in &UML;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Visual zastupljenost generalizacija u &UML; </phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Visual representation of a generalization in &UML;</para>"
msgstr "<para>Visual zastupljenost generalizacija u &UML; </para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Associations"
msgstr "Pridruženja"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An association represents a relationship between classes, and gives the "
"common semantics and structure for many types of <quote>connections</quote> "
"between objects."
msgstr ""
"Udruženje predstavlja odnos između klasa, i daje zajednički semantike i "
"strukture za mnoge vrste <quote>veza</quote> između objekata."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Associations are the mechanism that allows objects to communicate to each "
"other. It describes the connection between different classes (the connection "
"between the actual objects is called object connection, or <emphasis>link</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Udruženja su mehanizam koji omogućuje objektima da komuniciraju međusobno. "
"On opisuje vezu između različitih klasa (vezu između stvarne objektima se "
"zove objekat vezu, ili <emphasis>link</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Associations can have a role that specifies the purpose of the association "
"and can be uni- or bidirectional (indicates if the two objects participating "
"in the relationship can send messages to the other, of if only one of them "
"knows about the other). Each end of the association also has a multiplicity "
"value, which dictates how many objects on this side of the association can "
"relate to one object on the other side."
msgstr ""
"Pridruženja mogu imati ulogu koja određuje svrhu pridruživanja i može biti "
"jedno- ili dvosmjerno (pokazuje da ako dva objekta učestvuju u odnosima, oni "
"mogu slati poruke drugom, ako samo jedan od njih zna za drugog). Svaki kraj "
"pridruženja također ima mnoštvo vrijednosti, koje diktira koliko objekata na "
"ovoj strani pridruženja može se vezati na jedan objekt na drugoj strani."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, associations are represented as lines connecting the classes "
"participating in the relationship, and can also show the role and the "
"multiplicity of each of the participants. Multiplicity is displayed as a "
"range [min..max] of non-negative values, with a star (<literal>*</literal>) "
"on the maximum side representing infinite."
msgstr ""
"U &UML;, pridruženja su predstavljeni kao linija koje povezuju klase koje "
"učestvuju u relacijama, a može se pokazati ulogu i mnogostrukost svakog od "
"učesnika. Višestrukost se prikazuje kao niz [min..max] ne-negativnih "
"vrijednosti, sa zvjezdicom (<literal>*</literal>) na maksimalnoj strani koja "
"predstavlja beskonačno."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "&UML; Association"
msgstr "&UML; Pridruživanja"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Visual representation of an Association in &UML;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Vizuelna predstava pridruženja u &UML;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Visual representation of an Association in &UML;</para>"
msgstr "<para>Vizuelna predstava pridruženja u &UML;</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Aggregation</title>"
msgstr "<title>Agregacija</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Aggregations are a special type of associations in which the two "
"participating classes don't have an equal status, but make a <quote>whole-"
"part</quote> relationship. An Aggregation describes how the class that takes "
"the role of the whole, is composed (has) of other classes, which take the "
"role of the parts. For Aggregations, the class acting as the whole always "
"has a multiplicity of one."
msgstr ""
"Agregacije su posebna vrsta pridruženja u kojima su dvije klase učestvuju "
"nemaju ravnopravan status, ali napravi <quote>u cjelosti</quote> odnos. "
"Agregacija opisuje kako klasu koja preuzima ulogu u svemu, sastoji se (ima) "
"od drugih klasa, koje uzimaju ulogu dijelova. Za sažimanja, klasa koja "
"djeluje kao cijeli uvijek ima mnoštvo jednog."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, Aggregations are represented by an association that shows a rhomb "
"on the side of the whole."
msgstr ""
"U &UML;, sažimanja zastupa udruženje koje pokazuje romb na strani cjelini."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Aggregation</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Sažimanje</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>Visual representation of an Aggregation relationship in &UML;</"
"phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Vizualno zastupanje agregacije odnos u &UML;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>Visual representation of an Aggregation relationship in &UML;</para>"
msgstr "<para>Vizualno zastupanje agregacije odnos u &UML;</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Composition</title>"
msgstr "<title>Kompozicija</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Compositions are associations that represent <emphasis>very strong</"
"emphasis> aggregations. This means, Compositions form whole-part "
"relationships as well, but the relationship is so strong that the parts "
"cannot exist on its own. They exist only inside the whole, and if the whole "
"is destroyed the parts die too."
msgstr ""
"Kompozicije su udruženja koja predstavljaju <emphasis>vrlo jaku</emphasis> "
"agregaciju. To znači, Kompozicije čine cijelovit odnos, ali veza je toliko "
"jaka da se dijelovi ne mogu postojati samostalno. Oni postoje samo unutar "
"cjelini, a ako cijeli je uništio dijelove umiru."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UML;, Compositions are represented by a solid rhomb on the side of the "
"whole."
msgstr "U &UML;, Kompozicije su predstavljene solidnu romb na strani cjelini."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:355
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Composition</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Kompozicije</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Visual representation of a Composition relationship in &UML;"
msgstr "Vizuelna predstava kompozicije u &UML;"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Class Diagram Items"
msgstr "Ostali elementi Dijagrama Klasa"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "Class diagrams can contain several other items besides classes."
msgstr "Dijagrami klasa može sadržavati nekoliko drugih stavki osim klase."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interfaces"
msgstr "Interfejsi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:373
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Interfaces are abstract classes which means instances cannot be directly "
#| "created of them. They can contain operations but no attributes. Classes "
#| "can inherit from interfaces (through a realisation association) and "
#| "instances can then be made of these diagrams."
msgid ""
"Interfaces are abstract classes which means instances cannot be directly "
"created of them. They can contain operations but no attributes. Classes can "
"inherit from interfaces (through a realisation association) and instances "
"can then be made of these classes."
msgstr ""
"Interfejsi su apstraktne klase što znači instance se ne mogu izravno stvorio "
"od njih. Oni mogu sadržavati operacija, ali ne i atribute. Nastava se "
"nasljeđuju interfejsa (kroz realizaciju Association), a zatim slučajevima "
"može biti od ovih dijagrama."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid "Datatypes"
msgstr "Tipovi podataka"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Datatypes are primitives which are typically built into a programming "
"language. Common examples include integers and booleans. They cannot have "
"relationships to classes but classes can have relationships to them."
msgstr ""
"Tipovi podataka su primitive koje se obično ugrađeni u programski jezik. "
"Zajednički primjeri uključuju integers i Boolean. Oni ne mogu imati odnos "
"prema klasa, ali klase mogu imati odnose na njih."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enums"
msgstr "Enumi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enums are a simple list of values. A typical example is an enum for days of "
"the week. The options of an enum are called Enum Literals. Like datatypes "
"they cannot have relationships to classes but classes can have relationships "
"to them."
msgstr ""
"Enum su jednostavan lista vrijednosti. Tipičan primjer je enum danima u "
"tjednu. Opcije nekog enum nazivaju Enum Literali. Kao tipovi podataka ne "
"mogu imati odnos prema klasa, ali klase mogu imati odnose na njih."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Packages"
msgstr "Paketi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Packages represent a namespace in a programming language. In a diagram they "
"are used to represent parts of a system which contain more than one class, "
"maybe hundereds of classes."
msgstr ""
"Paketi predstavljaju imenske prostore u programskom jeziku. U dijagramu se "
"koriste da predstavljaju dijelove sistema koji sadrže više od jedne klase, "
"možda stotine klasa."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sequence Diagrams"
msgstr "Sekvenca Dijagrami"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:401
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sequence Diagrams show the message exchange (&ie; method call) between "
"several Objects in a specific time-delimited situation. Objects are "
"instances of classes. Sequence Diagrams put special emphasis in the order "
"and the times in which the messages to the objects are sent."
msgstr ""
"Sekvenca Dijagrami pokazuju razmjenu poruka (&ie; poziv metode) između više "
"objekata u određenom vremenskom odijeliti situaciju. Objekti su instance "
"klase. Sequence Dijagrami stavio poseban naglasak na red i vremena u kojima "
"se šalju poruke na objektima."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Sequence Diagrams objects are represented through vertical dashed lines, "
"with the name of the Object on the top. The time axis is also vertical, "
"increasing downwards, so that messages are sent from one Object to another "
"in the form of arrows with the operation and parameters name."
msgstr ""
"U Sekvenca Dijagramima objekti su predstavljeni kroz vertikalne isprekidanih "
"linija, uz ime objekta na vrhu. Vremenskoj osi je vertikalna, povećanje "
"prema dolje, tako da se poruke šalju iz jednog objekta na drugi u obliku "
"strijele sa operacije i parametara ime."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sequence Diagram"
msgstr "Dijagram sekvenci"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing a Sequence Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama Sekvenci</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:424
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing a Sequence Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama Sekvenci</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Messages can be either synchronous, the normal type of message call where "
"control is passed to the called object until that method has finished "
"running, or asynchronous where control is passed back directly to the "
"calling object. Synchronous messages have a vertical box on the side of the "
"called object to show the flow of program control."
msgstr ""
"Poruke mogu biti sinkroni, normalan tip poruke u kojoj se poziva prošli "
"kontrolu na pod nazivom objekta do tog metoda je završio trčanje, ili "
"asinkroni, gdje se prošli kontrolu nazad direktno na poziv objekta. Sinkroni "
"poruke imaju vertikalne kutiju na strani naziva objekta za prikaz protoka "
"kontrole programa."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:436
#, no-c-format
msgid "Collaboration Diagrams"
msgstr "Kolaboracija Dijagrami"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Collaboration Diagrams show the interactions occurring between the objects "
"participating in a specific situation. This is more or less the same "
"information shown by Sequence Diagrams but there the emphasis is put on how "
"the interactions occur in time while the Collaboration Diagrams put the "
"relationships between the objects and their topology in the foreground."
msgstr ""
"Kolaboracija Dijagrami pokazuju interakcije nastale između objekata koji "
"učestvuju u specifičnoj situaciji. To je manje-više iste informacije "
"pokazuju Sequence Dijagrami ali naglasak je stavljen na tome kako "
"interakcija javljaju u vremenu dok je Collaboration Dijagrami stavio odnose "
"između objekata i njihovih topologija u prvom planu."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Collaboration Diagrams messages sent from one object to another are "
"represented by arrows, showing the message name, parameters, and the "
"sequence of the message. Collaboration Diagrams are specially well suited to "
"showing a specific program flow or situation and are one of the best diagram "
"types to quickly demonstrate or explain one process in the program logic."
msgstr ""
"U Kolaboracija Dijagramima poruke poslane od jednog objekta na drugi zastupa "
"strelice, pokazujući ime poruke, parametri, a redoslijed poruke. Saradnja "
"Dijagrami su posebno pogodni za pokazuje određeni protok programa ili "
"situaciju i jedan od najboljih tipova dijagrama brzo pokazati ili objasniti "
"jedan proces u programu logiku."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "Collaboration"
msgstr "Kolaboracija"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing a Collaboration Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikaz Kolaboracija Dijagrama</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:459
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing a Collaboration Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikaz Kolaboracija Dijagrama</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>State Diagram</title>"
msgstr "<title>Dijagram Stanja</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"State Diagrams show the different states of an Object during its life and "
"the stimuli that cause the Object to change its state."
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami Stanja pokazuju različita stanja nekog objekta tokom svog života i "
"stimulansa koji uzrokuju objekta promijeniti svoje stanje."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"State Diagrams view Objects as <emphasis>state machines</emphasis> or finite "
"automates that can be in one of a set of finite states and that can change "
"its state via one of a finite set of stimuli. For example an Object of type "
"<emphasis>NetServer</emphasis> can be in one of following states during its "
"life:"
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami Stanja vide objekat kao <emphasis>mašine stanja</emphasis> ili "
"konačnih automata koji mogu biti u jednom od skupa konačnih država i da može "
"promijeniti svoje stanje preko jednog od konačan skup podražaja. Na primjer "
"objekat tipa <emphasis>NetServer</emphasis> može biti u jednom od sljedećih "
"stanja tokom svog života:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ready"
msgstr "Spremno"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Listening"
msgstr "Slušam"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working"
msgstr "Radi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stopped"
msgstr "Zaustavljen"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "and the events that can cause the Object to change states are"
msgstr "i događaje koji mogu izazvati objekta za promjenu stanja"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:484
#, no-c-format
msgid "Object is created"
msgstr "Objekat je kreiran"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:485
#, no-c-format
msgid "Object receives message listen"
msgstr "Objekat prima poruke slušaju"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:486
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Client requests a connection over the network"
msgstr "Klijent zahtijeva vezu preko mreže"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Client terminates a request"
msgstr "Klijent raskida zahtjev"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid "The request is executed and terminated"
msgstr "Zahtjev se izvršava i prestaje"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "Object receives message stop"
msgstr "Objekat prima poruku stop"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>etc</para>"
msgstr "<para>etc</para>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:494
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>State Diagram</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Dijagram Stanja</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:500
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing a State Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama Stanja</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:503
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing a State Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama Stanja</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:510
#, no-c-format
msgid "State"
msgstr "Stanje"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"States are the building block of State Diagrams. A State belongs to exactly "
"one class and represents a summary of the values the attributes of a class "
"can take. A &UML; State describes the internal state of an object of one "
"particular class"
msgstr ""
"Stanja su gradivni blok dijagrama stanja. Stanje pripada tačno jednoj klasi "
"i predstavlja sažetak vrijednosti atributa klase može potrajati. &UML; "
"stanje opisuje unutrašnje stanje objekta jedne određene klase"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that not every change in one of the attributes of an object should be "
"represented by a State but only those changes that can significantly affect "
"the workings of the object"
msgstr ""
"Imajte na umu da nije svaka promjena u jednom od atributa objekta treba "
"zastupa državi, ali samo one promjene koje mogu značajno utjecati na rad "
"objekta"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two special types of States: Start and End. They are special in "
"that there is no event that can cause an Object to return to its Start "
"state, in the same way as there is no event that can possible take an Object "
"out of its End state once it has reached it."
msgstr ""
"Postoje dvije posebne vrste stanja: početak i kraj. Oni su poseban po tome "
"što ne postoji događaj koji može izazvati objekta da se vrate u svoje "
"pocetak stanja, na isti način kao što nema događaja koji može moguće uzeti "
"objekta iz svoje krajnje stanje nakon što je završila."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:527
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activity Diagram"
msgstr "Dijagram aktivnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activity Diagrams describe the sequence of activities in a system with the "
"help of Activities. Activity Diagrams are a special form of State Diagrams, "
"that only (or mostly) contains Activities."
msgstr ""
"Dijagram aktivnosti opisuju slijed aktivnosti u sistemu uz pomoć aktivnosti. "
"Aktivnost Dijagrami su poseban oblik dijagrama stanja, da je samo (ili "
"uglavnom) sadrži aktivnosti."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example Activity Diagram."
msgstr "Primjer Dijagrama aktivnosti."

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:540
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&umbrello; showing an Activity Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama aktivnosti</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:543
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>&umbrello; showing an Activity Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>&umbrello; prikaz Dijagrama aktivnosti</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:549
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activity Diagrams are similar to procedural Flux Diagrams, with the "
"difference that all Activities are clearly attached to Objects."
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami aktivnosti su slične proceduralne Flux dijagrami, s tom razlikom "
"da se sve aktivnosti su jasno prilogu Objektima."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activity Diagrams are always associated to a <emphasis>Class</emphasis>, an "
"<emphasis>Operation</emphasis> or a <emphasis>Use Case</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami aktivnosti su uvijek povezani na <emphasis>Klasa</emphasis>, jedan "
"<emphasis> Operacija</emphasis> ili <emphasis>Use Case</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activity Diagrams support sequential as well as parallel Activities. "
"Parallel execution is represented via Fork/Wait icons, and for the "
"Activities running in parallel, it is not important the order in which they "
"are carried out (they can be executed at the same time or one after the "
"other)"
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami Aktivnosti podržava sekvencijalni, kao i paralelne aktivnosti. "
"Paralelno izvršenje predstavljeni preko Fork/Wait ikone, kao i za aktivnosti "
"radi paralelno, to nije važno je poredak u kojem se izvode (oni mogu biti "
"pogubljeni u isto vrijeme ili jedan za drugim)"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activity"
msgstr "Aktivnost"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An Activity is a single step in a process. One Activity is one state in the "
"system with internal activity and, at least, one outgoing transition. "
"Activities can also have more than one outgoing transition if they have "
"different conditions."
msgstr ""
"Aktivnost je jedan korak u procesu. Jedna aktivnost je jedno stanje u "
"sistemu sa internim aktivnost i, najmanje, jedan odlazeći tranzicije. "
"Aktivnosti mogu imati više od jednog odlazne tranzicije ako imaju različite "
"uvjete."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activities can form hierarchies, this means that an Activity can be composed "
"of several <quote>detail</quote> Activities, in which case the incoming and "
"outgoing transitions should match the incoming and outgoing transitions of "
"the detail diagram."
msgstr ""
"Aktivnosti mogu formirati hijerarhije, to znači da se aktivnost može se "
"sastojati od nekoliko <quote>detalj</quote> djelatnosti, u kojem slučaju se "
"ulazne i izlazne tranzicije treba odgovarati ulazne i izlazne tranzicije "
"dijagrama detalja."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:575
#, no-c-format
msgid "Helper Elements"
msgstr "Pomoćni Elementi"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are a few elements in &UML; that have no real semantic value for the "
"model, but help to clarify parts of the diagram. These elements are"
msgstr ""
"Postoji nekoliko elemenata u &UML; koji nemaju realne semantičku vrijednost "
"za model, ali pomoći da se razjasni dijelove dijagrama. Ovi elementi su"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:579
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text lines"
msgstr "Redovi teksta"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Notes and anchors"
msgstr "Redovi teksta i sidra"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boxes"
msgstr "Kutije"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Text lines are useful to add short text information to a diagram. It is free-"
"standing text and has no meaning to the Model itself."
msgstr ""
"Tekst linije su korisne za dodavanje kratke informacije tekst dijagram. To "
"je samostojeći tekst i nema smisla da sam model."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Notes are useful to add more detailed information about an object or a "
"specific situation. They have the great advantage that notes can be anchored "
"to &UML; Elements to show that the note <quote>belongs</quote> to a specific "
"object or situation."
msgstr ""
"Bilješke su korisne za dodavanje detaljnije informacije o objektu ili "
"specifičnu situaciju. Oni imaju veliku prednost koja napominje se može "
"usidren u &UML; Elementi koji pokazuju da napomenu <quote>pripada </quote> "
"na određeni predmet ili situaciju."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Boxes are free-standing rectangles which can be used to group items together "
"to make diagrams more readable. They have no logical meaning in the model."
msgstr ""
"Kutije su slobodno stojeći pravokutnika koji se može koristiti za grupu "
"predmeta zajedno kako bi dijagrama više čitati. Oni nemaju logično značenje "
"u modelu."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid "Component Diagrams"
msgstr "Dijagrami komponenti"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Component Diagrams show the software components (either component "
"technologies such as KParts, CORBA components or Java Beans or just sections "
"of the system which are clearly distinguishable) and the artifacts they are "
"made out of such as source code files, programming libraries or relational "
"database tables."
msgstr ""
"Komponentni dijagrami pokazuju komponenti softvera (ili komponenta "
"tehnologije kao što su KParts, CORBA komponente ili Java Beans ili samo "
"dijelovima sistema koji su jasno razlikovati) i artefakti su napravljeni od "
"kao što su izvorni kod datoteke, programiranje knjižnica ili relacijskih "
"tablica baze podataka ,"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Components can have interfaces (&ie; abstract classes with operations) that "
"allow associations between components."
msgstr ""
"Komponente mogu imati interfejse (&ie; apstraktne klase s operacijama) koje "
"omogućavaju udruženja između komponenti."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:611
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deployment Diagrams"
msgstr "Razvojni Dijagrami"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:613
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Deployment diagrams show the runtime component instances and their "
"associations. They include Nodes which are physical resources, typically a "
"single computer. They also show interfaces and objects (class instances)."
msgstr ""
"Razvojni Dijagrami pokazuju runtime komponentu instanci i njihova udruženja. "
"Oni uključuju Čvorovi koji su fizički resursi, obično jednom računaru. Oni "
"također pokazuju interfejsa i objekata (klasa instance)."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entity Relationship Diagrams"
msgstr "Dijagrami Odnosa Entiteta"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Entity Relationship Diagrams (ER Diagrams) show the conceptual design of "
"database applications. They depict the various entities (concepts) in the "
"information system and the existing relationships and constraints between "
"them. An extension of Entity Relationship Diagrams named 'Extended Entity "
"Relationship Diagrams' or 'Enhanced Entity Relationship Diagrams' (EER), are "
"used to incorporate Object Oriented design techniques in ER Diagrams."
msgstr ""
"Dijagrami Odnosa Entiteta (ER dijagrami) pokazuju idejnog projekta "
"aplikacija baze podataka. Oni opisuju različitih subjekata (koncepata) u "
"informacioni sistem i postojeće odnose i ograničenja između njih. Proširenje "
"Entity Relationship Dijagrami pod nazivom \"Extended Entity Relationship "
"Dijagrami 'ili' Enhanced Entity Relationship Dijagrami '(EER), koriste se "
"ugraditi Objektno orijentirano tehnikama dizajna u ER dijagram."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:627
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example Entity Relationship diagram."
msgstr "Primjer Dijagrama Odnosa Entiteta."

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Umbrello showing an Entity Relationship Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Umbrello prikazuje Dijagrami Odnosa Entiteta</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Umbrello showing an Entity Relationship Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>Umbrello prikazuje Dijagrami Odnosa Entiteta</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entity"
msgstr "Entitet"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>Entity</emphasis> is any concept in the real world with an "
"independent existence. It may be an object with a physical existence "
"( example, Computer, Robot) or it may be an object with a conceptual "
"existence ( eq: University Course). Each entity has a set of attributes "
"which describe the properties of the Entity."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Entitet</emphasis> je bilo koncept u stvarnom svijetu sa "
"nezavisnim postojanja. To može biti predmet sa fizičkim postojanjem "
"(primjer, Computer, Robot) ili može biti objekt s konceptualnim postojanja "
"(eq: University Course). Svaki entitet ima skup atributa koji opisuju "
"svojstva entiteta."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Note:</emphasis> No standard notations exist for depicting ER "
"Diagrams. Different texts on this subject use different notations. The "
"concepts and notations for EER diagrams used in Umbrello are from the "
"following book : <emphasis>Elmasri R. and Navathe S. (2004). Fundamentals of "
"Database Systems 4th edn. Addison Wesley</emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Napomena:</emphasis> Nema standardne notacije za predstavu ER "
"dijagrama. Različiti tekstovi na ovu temu koriste različite notacije. "
"Koncepti i formate za EER dijagrami koji se koriste u Umbrello su iz "
"sljedeće knjige: <emphasis>Elmasri R. i Navathe S. (2004). Osnove Database "
"Systems 4. izd. Addison Wesley </emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In an ER Diagram, Entities are represented by rectangles, with the name of "
"the entity at the top, and can also show the attributes of the entity in "
"another <quote>compartment</quote> inside the rectangle."
msgstr ""
"U ER Dijagram, entiteti su predstavljene pravougaonika, sa imenom entiteta "
"na vrhu, a može se pokazati atribute entiteta u drugom <quote> pregrade </"
"quote> unutar pravokutnika."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:655
#, no-c-format
msgid "An Entity in an ER Diagram;"
msgstr "Jedan entiteta u ER Dijagramu;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:661
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Visual representation of an entity in an ER Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Vizualna zastupljenost entiteta u ER Dijagramu</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:664
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Visual representation of an entity in an ER Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>Vizualna zastupljenost entiteta u ER Dijagramu</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:671
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entity Attributes"
msgstr "Atributi entiteta"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:672
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In ER Diagrams , Entity Attributes are shown with their name in a different "
"compartment of the Entity to which they belong."
msgstr ""
"U ER dijagrama, entiteta atributi su prikazani sa svojim imenom u različitim "
"pregradu entiteta kojem pripadaju."

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:677
#, no-c-format
msgid "Constraints"
msgstr "Ograničenja"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:678
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Constraints in ER Diagrams specify the restrictions on data in the "
"information schema."
msgstr ""
"Ograničenja u ER Dijagrami navesti ograničenja podataka u informacijskom "
"shemi."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are four types of constraints supported in Umbrello :"
msgstr "Postoje četiri vrste ograničenja podržani u Umbrello:"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Primary Key:</emphasis> The set of attributes declared as "
"<emphasis>primary key</emphasis> are unique to the entity. There can be only "
"one primary key in an Entity and none of its constituent attributes can be "
"NULL."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis> primarni ključ: </emphasis>Skup atributa proglašen "
"<emphasis>primarni ključ</emphasis> su jedinstveni entitet. Tu može biti "
"samo jedan primarni ključ u entiteta i nijedan od njenih konstitutivnih "
"atributa može biti NULL."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Unique Key:</emphasis> The set of attributes declared as "
"<emphasis>unique</emphasis> are unique to the entity. There can be many "
"unique constraints on an Entity. Its constituent attributes can be NULL. "
"Unique Keys and Primary Keys uniquely identify a row in a table ( entity )"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Jedinstveni Ključ: </emphasis> Skup atributa proglašen <emphasis> "
"jedinstveni </emphasis> su jedinstveni entitet. Ne može biti mnoge "
"jedinstvene ograničenja na jednog entiteta. Njenih konstitutivnih atributa "
"može biti NULL. Jedinstveni ključevi i primarne ključeve jedinstveno "
"identificirati red u tablici (entitet)"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:693
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Foreign Key:</emphasis> A Foreign Key is a referential constraint "
"between two tables. The foreign key identifies a column or a set of columns "
"in one (referencing) table that refers to a column or set of columns in "
"another (referenced) table. The columns in the referenced table must form a "
"primary key or unique key."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis> Strani Ključ: </emphasis> stranog ključa je referentnog "
"ograničenja između dva stola. Strani ključ identificira stupac ili skup "
"stupaca u jednom (referenci) tablicu koja se odnosi na stupac ili skup "
"stupaca u drugom (navedeni) stol. Kolone u referentna tablica mora formirati "
"primarni ključ ili jedinstveni ključ."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Check Constraint:</emphasis> A check constraint (also known as "
"table check constraint) is a condition that defines valid data when adding "
"or updating an entry in a table of a relational database. A check constraint "
"is applied to each row in the table. The constraint must be a predicate. It "
"can refer to a single or multiple columns of the table."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis> provjere ograničenja: </emphasis> Provjera ograničenja (poznat i "
"kao stol provjere ograničenja) je stanje koje definira važeće podatke "
"prilikom dodavanja ili ažuriranja unos u tablici od relacijskih baza "
"podataka. Provjera ograničenja se primjenjuju na svaki red u tablici. "
"Ograničenje mora biti predikat. To se može odnositi na jedan ili više "
"stupaca tablice."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:701
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: price >= 0"
msgstr "Primjer: cijena> = 0"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extended Entity Relationship (EER) Diagram Concepts"
msgstr "Prošireni Entity Relationship (EER) Dijagram Koncept"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specialization"
msgstr "Specijalizacija"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specialization is a way to form new entities using entities that have "
"already been defined. The new entities, known as derived entities, take over "
"(or inherit) attributes of the pre-existing entities, which are referred to "
"as base entities . It is intended to help reuse existing data with little or "
"no modification."
msgstr ""
"Specijalizacija je način da se formira novi entiteti koriste subjekata koji "
"su već definirani. Nova lica, poznat kao izvedena entiteta, preuzeti (ili "
"naslijediti) atribute od već postojeće entiteta, koji se nazivaju bazu "
"entiteta. Namjera je da se pomogne ponovno korištenje postojeće podatke sa "
"malo ili bez modifikacija."

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "In Umbrello, one can specify Disjoint and Overlapping Specialization"
msgstr "U Umbrello, može se odrediti disjunktnih i Preklapanje Specijalizacija"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disjoint Specialization"
msgstr "Disjunktne Specijalizacije"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:718
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Disjoint Specialization specifies that the subclasses of the specialization "
"must be disjoint. This means that an entity can be a member of at most one "
"of the derived entities of the specialization"
msgstr ""
"Disjunktna Specijalizacija određuje da podklase specijalizacije mora biti "
"razdvojen. To znači da entitet može biti član najviše jedan od izvedenih "
"entiteta specijalizacije"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:721
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entities taking part in Disjoint Specialization"
msgstr "Entiteta učestvovali u disjunktnih Specijalizacija"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:727
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>Visual representation of Disjoint Specialization in EER Diagram</"
"phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>Vizualna reprezentacija disjunktnih Specijalizacija u EER Dijagram</"
"phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>Visual representation of Disjoint Specialization in EER Diagram</para>"
msgstr ""
"<para>Vizualna reprezentacija disjunktnih Specijalizacija u EER Dijagram</"
"para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overlapping Specialization"
msgstr "Preklapanje Specijalizacija"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:739
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the derived entities are not constrained to be disjoint, their set of "
"entities are said to be in overlapping specialization. This means that the "
"same real world entity may be a member of more than one derived entity of "
"the specialization"
msgstr ""
"Kada su izvedeni entiteta nisu ograničeni da budu disjunktnih, njihov set "
"subjekata se kaže da su u preklapanja specijalizacije. To znači da se isti "
"stvarnom svijetu subjekt može biti član više od jednog izvedena entitet "
"specijalizacije"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:742
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entities taking part in Overlapping Specialization"
msgstr "Entiteti učestvovali u preklapanje Specijalizacija"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>Visual representation of Overlapping Specialization in EER Diagram</"
"phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>Vizualna zastupljenost Preklapanje Specijalizacija u EER Dijagram</"
"phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:751
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>Visual representation of Overlapping Specialization in EER Diagram</"
"para>"
msgstr ""
"<para>Vizualna zastupljenost Preklapanje Specijalizacija u EER Dijagram</"
"para>"

#. Tag: title
#: uml_basics.docbook:760
#, no-c-format
msgid "Category"
msgstr "Kategorija"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A derived Entity is said to be a <emphasis>Category</emphasis> when it "
"represents a collection of objects that is a subset of Union of the distinct "
"entity types. A Category is modelled when the need arises for a single "
"superclass/subclass relationship with more than one superclass, where the "
"superclasses represent different entity types. ( Much like multiple "
"inheritance in Object Oriented Programming )."
msgstr ""
"Izvedeni Entitet se kaže da je a <emphasis> Kategorija </emphasis> kada "
"predstavlja kolekciju predmeta koji je podskup unije različita tipa "
"entiteta. A kategorija je po uzoru kada javlja se potreba za jednim "
"superklase / potklasa odnos sa više od jednog superklase, gdje superclasses "
"predstavljaju različite vrste entiteta. (Slično kao i više nasljedstva u "
"Object Oriented Programming)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: uml_basics.docbook:766
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entities taking part in a Category relationship"
msgstr "Entiteta učestvovali u kategoriji odnosa"

#. Tag: phrase
#: uml_basics.docbook:772
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Visual representation of a Category in EER Diagram</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Vizualna zastupljenost kategorije u EER Dijagram</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: uml_basics.docbook:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Visual representation of a Category in EER Diagram</para>"
msgstr "<para>Vizualna zastupljenost kategorije u EER Dijagram</para>"
